## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-111">L'esempio seguente usa il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> elemento da compilare elenchi di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> elementi contenente i nomi di paese, uno dei quali è possibile utilizzare per riconoscere la contenente una frase.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-111">The following example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> element to build lists of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> elements containing country names, any one of which may be used to recognize the containing phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-112">L'esempio aggiunge quindi uno dei risultante <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetti per le rispettive norme per paesi europei e paesi dell'America del sud.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-112">The example then adds one of the resulting <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects to their respective rules for European countries and South American countries.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-113">Inoltre, l'esempio utilizza il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetto gruppo di riferimenti regola a `ruleEurope` e `ruleSAmerica` in un elenco di alternative a due, dei due di che possono essere utilizzati per riconoscere l'input vocale.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-113">Further on, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to group rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` into a list of two alternatives, either one of which may be used to recognize spoken input.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-116">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali" seguito dal nome di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-116">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-117">Crea una regola pubblica denominata `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-117">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-118">Crea quindi due <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> degli oggetti mediante <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetti che contengono matrici di nuovo <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-118">It then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects that contain arrays of new <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-119">Per visualizzare la grammatica di questo esempio genera l'errore, vedere <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-119">To see the grammar that this example generates, see <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.%23ctor%2A>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
 public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-124">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali" seguito dal nome di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-124">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-125">Nell'esempio viene utilizzato il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> elemento da compilare elenchi di nomi di paese accettabili da una matrice di <xref:System.String> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-125">The example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> element to build lists of acceptable country names from an array of <xref:System.String> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-126">L'esempio aggiunge quindi uno dei risultante <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetti per le rispettive norme per paesi europei e paesi dell'America del sud.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-126">The example then adds one of the resulting <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects to their respective rules for European countries and South American countries.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
    // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf (new string[] {"England","France","Germany","Italy"});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf (new string[] {"Argentina","Brazil","Uruguay"});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  srgsGrammar.Rules.Add (new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-131">L'esempio seguente crea una grammatica che riconosce la frase "è di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali" seguito dal nome di un paese che ha vinto i mondiali.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-131">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-132">Nell'esempio viene utilizzato il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetto per creare elenchi di nomi di paese accettabili da una matrice di <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> oggetti.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-132">The example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to build lists of acceptable country names from an array of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="90ac3-133">Utilizzando il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf.Add%2A> metodo, l'esempio aggiunge un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> che contiene la stringa "Italy" per il <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> oggetto `oneOfEurope`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="90ac3-133">Using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem> that contains the string "Italy" to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object `oneOfEurope`.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany")});  
  oneOfEurope.Add(new SrgsItem("Italy"));  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
